*------------------------------------*
| Compute the thickness distribution |
*------------------------------------*

Inputs : 
--------

1) SDF values in two columns ( the values must be i the second, the first has no importance )
2) the precision for the histogramm ( i.e the length of the subintervals, ex : 3 -> [0,max/3] [max/3, 2max/3], 
and [2max/3,max] ). 

Outputs : 
---------

1) The repartition in a .txt file containing 2 columns : values/frequency
2) A gnuplot script to plot the rerpartition. 

To compile  :
-------------

g++ -Wall distribution.cpp -o distribution

To use :
--------

./distribution path/to/the/sdf/values.txt precision

example :

./distribution sdf_values.txt 100

By experiment, 100 seems to be a good value for pretty distributions ;-)


